com.esri.mo2.map.dpy
Interface MapFilter

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, QueryFilter, SpatialFilter
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseMapFilter
public interface MapFilter
extends SpatialFilter

A MapFilter is a kind of SpatialFilter that is specific to a Map Display. When a Map wants to draw data represented by a map Layer, the Layer prepares a MapFilter that is passed to its associated Dataset. The Dataset must ensure that appropriate data is obtained and available for Layer to be drawn on the Map Display. Optionally the Dataset can choose to influence the data retrieval using the Map Display's DisplayTransform - for instance, a MapServer will use the transform to retrieve an image whose pixel size exactly matches the Display pixel size. Also, an IFClient may choose to reduce the size of retrieved data using a scale dependency stategy.

See Also:
DisplayArea, SpatialFilter, Dataset, Data
